					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-899005#post-2059127</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-899005/the-broken-mind#post-2059127</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 26 Jun 2014 20:18:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>HammerMaiden</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1552358</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>First example of CotBG Holy Writ in formal form. This is a document from the Mainline Broken Church, and is one of the last chapters of the Book of Pieces, a chronicle of the first gathering of all the pieces of the Broken God.</p> <p>The SCP being referenced<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-554437-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup> is of course linked, and though it isn't currently recognized as a CotBG skip, I couldn't <em>not</em> use it. It was just too perfect.</p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-554437-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. Okay, a <em>lot</em> of SCP's are referenced, but it's not really <em>about</em> them.</div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
